8}_{-0.379}$. We find that including\nsmaller scales while marginalizing over non-linear galaxy bias improves the\nconstraining power in the $\\Omega_m-S_8$ plane by $31$% and in the $\\Omega_m-w$\nplane by $41$% while yielding consistent cosmological parameters from those in\nthe linear bias case. These results are combined with those from cosmic shear\nin a companion paper to present full DES-Y3 constraints from the three\ntwo-point functions (3x2pt).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 May 2021 01:58:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 21 Dec 2022 19:11:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-23"}
